 Butterworth - Butterworth police arrested a 35-year-old man for alleged murder of a 51-year-old man over the weekend. "It is alleged that the 51-year-old man was stabbed on Sunday, at about 20:00, at Sigingqini Locality, Mission Village, Butterworth. "The deceased suffered upper body injuries and was rushed to Butterworth Hospital where he later passed away," said police spoesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The motive behind the murder is not known. "The 35-year-old suspect was traced and arrested." Capt Manatha said that the suspect is due to appear before the Butterworth Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. "The deceased was identified as Khaya Rayi, aged 51," he added. "He is believed to be from Mdantsane Township outside East London." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 